    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Cook for 3 min or until the mushrooms have softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy vegetable stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>creamy vegetable stock</strong> and <strong>gnocchi</strong> to the pot with the softened mushrooms<strong> </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 7-8 min, or until the liquid has started to thicken and the gnocchi is cooked through</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gnocchi is cooking, pat your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper and season with<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>fish </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side, or until browned and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the gnocchi is cooked and the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until it wilts</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> gnocchi, mushrooms & spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-cod-with-gnocchi-mushrooms-and-spinach/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried fish </strong>over the <strong>gnocchi, mushrooms & spinach</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
